{"ID":270383, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"383\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs382.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs384.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 383<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">the guard, &ldquo;Let the old gentleman come in, he is my uncle.&rdquo;  The guard replied they did not care who\n  the hell he was uncle to, he should not go in.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Joseph replied, &ldquo;You will not hinder so old and infirm a man as he is from coming in,&rdquo; and then\n  said, &ldquo;Come in, uncle;&rdquo; on which, after searching him closely the guard let him pass into the jail,\n  where he remained about an hour. He asked Joseph if he thought he should again get out of the\n  hands of his enemies,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> when he replied, &ldquo;My brother Hyrum thinks I shall. I wish you would tell the\n  brethren in Macedonia that they can see by this, that it has not been safe for me to visit them; and\n  tell Almon W. Babbitt<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> I want him to come and assist me as an attorney at my expected trial\n  tomorrow before Captain R. F. Smith. (June 26, 1844.) DHC 6:597-598.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Last Night in Jail<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">June 26, 1844, 9:15 p.m.&mdash;Elder John Taylor prayed. Willard Richards, John Taylor,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> John S.\n  Fullmer, Stephen Markham and Dan Jones stayed with Joseph and Hyrum in the front room.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">During the evening the Patriarch Hyrum Smith read and commented upon extracts from the\n  Book of Mormon, on the imprisonment and deliverance of the servants of God for the Gospel&rsquo;s\n  sake.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> Joseph bore a powerful testimony to the guards of the divine authenticity of the Book of\n  Mormon, the restoration of the Gospel, the administration of angels, and that the kingdom of God\n  was again established upon the earth, for the sake of which he was then incarcerated<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> in that prison,\n  and not because he had violated any law<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> of God or man.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">They retired to rest late. Joseph and Hyrum occupied the only bedstead in the room, while their\n  friends lay side by side on the mattresses on the floor. Dr. Richards sat up writing until his last\n  candle left him in the dark. The report of a gun fired close by caused Joseph to rise, leave the bed,\n  and lay himself on the floor, having Dan Jones on his left, and John S. Fullmer on his right. Joseph\n  laid out his right arm, and said to John S. Fullmer, &ldquo;Lay your head on my arm for a pillow, Brother\n  John;&rdquo; and when all were quiet they conversed in a low tone about the prospects of their\n  deliverance.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> Joseph gave expression to several presentiments that he had to die, and said, &ldquo;I would\n  like to see my family again,&rdquo; and &ldquo;I would<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111137\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111137)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111137)\">2 Ne. 4:31<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111463\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111463)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111463)\">Omni 1:7<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113175\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113175)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113175)\">D&amp;C 8:4<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115555\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115555)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115555)\">D&amp;C 109:28<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116013\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116013)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116013)\">D&amp;C 124:84<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116060\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116060)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116060)\">D&amp;C 124:129<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111586\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111586)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111586)\">Mosiah 7:7-8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111607\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111607)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111607)\">Mosiah 12:17<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111683\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111683)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111683)\">Mosiah 21:23<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111853\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111853)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111853)\">Alma 8:31<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111871\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111871)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111871)\">Alma 9:32-33<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111964\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111964)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111964)\">Alma 14:17,27-28<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112009\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112009)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112009)\">Alma 20:2,5,22,24,28<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112013\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112013)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112013)\">Alma 21:15<\/a><\/spa